Who said burgers have to be greasy to be good? Meet this veggie-packed, air-fried Sooji Burger—crispy on the outside, soft and spicy on the inside, and totally guilt-free!

Bringing you this soulful recipe straight from the “Acchai Ki Rasoi”! It’s perfect for a fun tea-time treat or a light dinner with a twist.

Here’s how to make the patty:
In a pan, add:
• 1 cup water
• 1 tsp ginger
• 1 green chilli
• 3 tsp Gaaychaap red chilli powder
• Salt to taste

Bring to a boil and stir in:
• 1/2 cup Uttam semolina (sooji)

Once thickened, mix in:
• 1/2 cup boiled potato
• 1/4 cup boiled green peas
• 1/4 cup boiled corn
• 1/4 cup capsicum
• 1/2 cup coriander leaves

Shape into patties and air-fry at 200°C for 25 minutes, until golden and crisp!

To assemble the burger:
Layer your patty in a toasted bun with lettuce, onions, tomatoes, a cheese slice, and a generous dollop of burger sauce or mayo.

Save this recipe for your next burger night—and tag a foodie friend who’s always up for a hatke snack!

Creamcheese Chicken Salad🥹♥️

Ingredient list:-

🍽️For creamcheese 

Milk
2 tbsp vinegar or lemon juice
Cold water- for rinsing

- Boil milk in a kadhai, then switch off th flame & after 2 minutes, add vinegar. Then drain using a muslin cloth. 
- Rinse it with cold water 
- in a mixer, add the prepared chenna, add 2 tbsp drained water,

🍽️Veggies 

1/4 cup carrot
1/4 cup cucumber
1/4 cup beetroot
1 small onion
1/2 cup lettuce
2 -3 tbsp italian seasonings 
1 tsp black pepper powder
Salt as per taste

🍽️ Air fried chicken

200 grams boneless chicken
3 tbsp curd
1 tbsp ginger garlic paste
1 tsp turmeric powder 
2 tbsp red chilli powder 
1 tsp garam masala
1 tsp black pepper powder 
1/2 tbsp cumin powder 
3 tsp coriander powder 
Juice of 1/2 lemon

Optional- while air frying coat with some mixture of oil + red chilli powder, for that extra kick😋😍

Veg kurma recipe♥️

Ingredient list:-

For kurma paste:-
Half fresh coconut or 1/2 cup dessicated coconut
30 cashews
1 tbsp Chana dal
1 tbsp coriander seeds
1 tbsp Fennel seeds
1 tbsp Cumin seeds 
2 green chillies 
4 garlic cloves
1 inch ginger 
5 peppercorns
2 black cloves
2 tbsp Poppy seeds ( khas khas )
Add little water to make smooth paste

For curry:-

3 tbsp Oil
1 onion
1 tsp turmeric 
2 tbsp Red chilli powder 
2 bay leaves 
1 tomato 
1 carrot
1 cup green peas 
1/2 cup cauliflower 
1 small potato
Water as per required
Salt as per taste 
Some chopped coriander.

Note:- after adding kurma paste, cook it for 5-10 mins on low flame, then add in other ingredients.

Meet Meghana Kadu, Deputy Manager – Retail IT at Reliance Retail.
She didn’t dream of being a chef as a child. But during the lockdown, a spark turned into a passion project and her food blog Chef ModeOn now has 208K+ followers and over 150 brand collaborations, all built alongside her full-time job.

From working with Amazon & Oreo to setting up a home studio in her bedroom. Meghana’s story is proof that your profession doesn’t have to limit your passion.
